TY  - JOUR
AU  - Ellul, Andrew
AU  - Erel, Isil
AU  - Rajan, Uday
T1  - The COVID-19 Pandemic Crisis and Corporate Finance
PY  - 2020
Y1  - 2020/11/01
DO  - 10.1093/rcfs/cfaa016
JO  - The Review of Corporate Finance Studies
JA  - Review of Corporate Finance Studies
VL  - 9
IS  - 3
SP  - 421
EP  - 429
SN  - 2046-9128
AB  - The COVID-19 pandemic can be considered the third major shock to have hit the United States and the global economy in the first two decades of this century. First, we experienced the September 11, 2001, terror attacks, then the 2008–2009 Financial Crisis, and now the COVID-19 pandemic. Each of these crises confronted the global economy, and the financial system in particular, with different challenges, with the COVID-19 crisis likely to be the worst. According to the World Bank (2020), the global economy is expected to shrink by 5.2% this year, representing the deepest global recession since the Second World War.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rcfs/cfaa016
ER  - 



